2. peter@peter-laptop:~/github$ sudo apt-get install mediawiki

3. sudo apt-get install python-xml
http://moinmo.in/MoinMoinDependencies 

and many nice tools here, like pdf2text

===
below is the tarball installstion, which is a nicer way suggested here:
http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=1042931
  517  python setup.py install --prefix='/usr/local' --record=install.log
//since I am not root, I can not use /usr/local/  
522  mkdir others/mino
  528  cd moin-1.8.5/
  530  python setup.py install --prefix='/home/peter/others/mino' --record=install.log
  532  vim install.log
//every thing is in /home/peter/others/mino, really clean

=== Hard Requirements ===
The only hard requirement MoinMoin has is that you have Python >= 2.3 installed. 
